Overview
Today's session focused on solving the "Latency vs. Security" paradox. By treating the local machine as a temporary "Sanctuary," we moved beyond simple file syncing into Active Systems Orchestration.

Key Accomplishments
Transient Workspace Optimization

Transitioned execution from virtualized cloud drives to local silicon buffers.

Utilized directory junctions to maintain logical path consistency while maximizing physical disk throughput.

Cryptographic Identity Anchoring

Provisioned a local Certificate Authority to whitelist the core engine.

Bypassed "Unauthorized Access" blocks by establishing a verified hardware-handshake.

The "Ghost" Lifecycle Logic

Engineered a terminal-integrated dehydration sequence.

Integrated a mandatory Checksum Gate: The system physically blocks the exit if the local-to-cloud sync is not at 100% parity.

Automated the "Shift:Delete" vaporization of the local path (C:\SAIHV_TEMP) to ensure zero forensic trace.

Decentralized Orchestration

Created an external .manifest logic anchor.

The system is now "Self-Aware" of its state, meaning it can land on any hardware and immediately enforce its own security and sync rules without manual intervention.

